A suggestion for goal settings.... what do you say?

Goal 1: Modernize Promotion Components (Business)
Specific: I will develop a new, future-proof promotion component to replace the current complex UI components used in Verso.
Measurable: The new component will reduce the code size of the legacy components by at least 50%, significantly reduce the number of GraphQL queries, and replace at least three existing legacy components.
Attractive: The new solution will improve long-term maintainability and the ability to evolve the platform.
Realistic: I will build on existing insights from the project team and implement the solution in clearly defined, modular phases.
Time-bound: The first production-ready version of the new OneNav Ribbon component will be implemented and integrated by June 30, 2025.

Goal 2: Consolidate ContentHeader (Business)
Specific: I will consolidate the existing content header components in Verso into a new, future-proof ContentHeader component.
Measurable: The number of header variants will be reduced from 34 to five, and the corresponding codebase will be streamlined accordingly.
Attractive: The new component will improve clarity, reusability, and reduce technical maintenance overhead.
Realistic: The implementation will follow an iterative approach, starting with an analysis and concept phase in the first half of the year.
Time-bound: A stable, production-ready version of OneCover will be available in the live system by August 15, 2025.

Goal 3: Support personal growth within realistic boundaries (Personal)
Specific: I will support my professional and personal development within the scope of my daily work, especially through exchange with colleagues and interdisciplinary teams.
